🌐 WhiteNet – Identity-First Secure Network Protocol
A next-generation network architecture where identity is the foundation, not an afterthought.

🚀 Overview
WhiteNet is a secure, identity-first networking system that assigns every node a cryptographically verifiable identity bound to a unique IPv6 address.

Unlike traditional networks where trust is implicit, WhiteNet enforces a Zero Trust model, ensuring that:

Every node is verified

Every interaction is authenticated

Every attack attempt is detectable

🔐 Core Innovation
✅ Certified IPv6 Identity Issuance
Each node is assigned:

A unique IPv6 address

A cryptographically signed certificate issued by a trusted authority

IPv6 Address ↔ Certificate ↔ Public Key ↔ Identity
👉 This makes:

Impersonation ❌ impossible

Spoofing ❌ structurally prevented

🧠 Architecture
🏗️ WhiteNet Protocol Stack
┌──────────────────────────────┐
│  Application Layer           │
├──────────────────────────────┤
│  Secure Transport Layer      │ ← VPN-like (secure send)
├──────────────────────────────┤
│  Handshake Layer             │ ← TLS-like authentication
├──────────────────────────────┤
│  Trust Layer                 │ ← Verification engine
├──────────────────────────────┤
