└──────────────────────────────┘
⚙️ Features
🔑 1. PKI-Based Identity
RSA key pair per node

CA-signed certificates

Tamper-proof identity verification

🌐 2. IPv6 Identity Binding
Each identity mapped to a unique IPv6

Prevents IP spoofing

🔐 3. TLS-like Handshake
Simulated secure handshake:

Certificate validation

Challenge-response authentication

Secure channel establishment

🛡️ 4. Zero Trust Communication
Nodes must be verified before communication

Unauthorized nodes are blocked

🌍 5. DNSSEC-like Resolution (Simulated)
Domain → IPv6 mapping

Verified using trust engine

⚔️ 6. Security Resilience Engine
Simulates real-world attacks:

Attack Type	Protection Mechanism
Spoofing	Certificate verification
MITM	Signature validation
Sybil Attack	Identity filtering
Certificate Forgery	CA signature enforcement
💻 CLI Usage
▶️ Run CLI
python cli.py
🔑 Issue Certificate
python cli.py issue --user <username>
🌐 Bind IPv6
python cli.py bind --cert cert.json
🔍 Verify Node
python cli.py verify --ipv6 <address>
🔐 Handshake (TLS Simulation)
python cli.py handshake --ipv6 <address>
📡 Secure Communication
python cli.py send --from <ipv6_1> --to <ipv6_2>
🌍 Resolve Domain
python cli.py resolve --domain example.com
⚔️ Attack Simulation
python cli.py spoof-test
or

python cli.py security-demo
